<br>
     I've always read in these boards the Druids saying things regarding they having full agro, and that if you had agro it's your own damn fault...  Well, I felll to the fate of some of you who died cause a druid is clueless as to how to play their class.  <br>
<br>
    I'm fighting in EW near Safe tree last night, My warrior is figthing an Uthork warrior with cleric behind him.  Well, this druid run through with his snare warrior...   He runs <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> too far</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> from his mob, and my warrior becomes a new target.  So my warrior has 2 mobs hitting on him... so I go, oh well I can handle this...  I get near finishing the main mob, druid comes and picks his up.  So I shrug it off, didn't cause any real damage.   A bit later, while my warrior is pulling (I play 2 accounts) I didn't realize that I had yet another snared mob dropped on me... but on my Cleric this time.  Well, I dump all the loots on him cause warrior needs to pull... so cleric can't run.   I root it, but by the time my warrior got to it... it broke root, and finished my cleric.<br>
<br>
     I found out later that another group had the same incident happening to them, and I ended rezzing someone in their group.<br>
<br>
    My biggest mistake, considering I never got the name of the Druid in question (Only saw this wolf running through me over and over, never Targetted him).  I went to ooc and asked that Druids please be carefull with their kitting...   And I got flamed to hell for it and was also called a whiner and told that I shouldn't be spamming the zone...   So I was spamming the zone, on my first &quot;ooc&quot;... *Boggle*<br>
<br>
    Eitherway.   It's clear that I understood one thing.   Druids might not realize this when they keep crossing other people/group with their mobs.   They have <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> sow</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, mob is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> snared</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  In so, if they don't pay attention they will get out of agro range and if mob has another possible target around it <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> will</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->change to it if that target is KOS.  The none-sense Bull Shit I hear about Druids saying, I had full Agro on me... you must have done something...  Is full of crap.   If you go too far from your mob, your agro is Meaningless if there is a KOS target near mob.  Mob will <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> always</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> got for nearest target in it's agro range when the Druid is out of range.  This doesn't cause a problem when mobs aren't KOS to others, like Rhinos, Mammoth's, bears and many other mobs.  But this really screws other people off when the mobs are very easy to agro to begin with.<br>
<br>
Lesson to be learned ?   Don't go through people when you Kite...   If you don't have a choice, take notice of your distance so that you don't screw other people in the process.   Being considerate is a good trait in EQ, so I hope some Druids that have been doing this would be a bit more of that in the future. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/ukinoel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinoel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.sluggy.net/beta_forums/images/smiles/lilkiki.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here...get out</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/28/02 8:56:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2494.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kitting, and things Druid need to realize...</span><hr size=1> Excellent post, but sadly useless. This argument has been going on for ever, but until the druid has it done to himself, well... He wont acknowledge it.<br>
<br>
And that is especially true when kiting.<br>
<br>
And for the record, this seems to be especially true in the 30s and 40s, when the druid just begins to kite or quad kite. They seem a little bit more considerate in their 50s. <p><center>
<b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=132888 "> Kinoel Feuerfaust </a> \\//  <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=144553"> Ryolas Songdivine </a></b><br>
<i>Artificial intelligence is no match for natural stupidity.</i>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/udigilos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>digilos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/28/02 9:23:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2494.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kitting, and things Druid need to realize...</span><hr size=1> I've seen some level 60s do it in ME on a regular basis.<br>
<br>
Druids will always do it, wizards too.. No matter how many times it happens to them on other chars, there will always be some &quot;me &gt; anyone else&quot; so screw everyone else and what they care.<br>
<br>
Mind you, there are a lot of druids that will die before letting aggro get on another group. <br>
<br>
The best is when the main tank is low on HP while a cleric &quot;aggressively&quot; complete heals him.  I've seen druid quad's go &quot;Oh by that guy over there is almost dead, let's go help Fred!&quot; and kill the MT then go back after the druid who is glad to have the extra click to med.<br>
<br>
One of the places that makes my eyes roll for quad kiting (Unless I'm a chanter in a duo just sitting and playing buffer of course <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) is the rockhoppers.  Sometimes you see 2 or 3 duos or lower level groups out in the field happy as can be until a quad'r comes by and makes it 1) harder to get a spawn 2) have to watch the quad's pathing because you can get beat up easily by their kites.  I hate to see quad kiters come to a place where people are grabbing a majority of the spawns and then start quad'n and getting in the way or taking the peeps spawns.<br>
<br>
I know some of you are like FFA! You can't camp whatever.. well then don't ask me for clarity (So they can regen mana from their quad killing and then sit next to me where I'm medding).. there are a few druids/wizards out there scowling at me for not buffing them for that reason.  If we're after the same mobs and I find what you're doing annoying.. don't even ask you won't get it.  I don't care if you do sow me, I'm not obligated to return anything to you other than a thanks if I see it.<br>
<br>
Things like this are part of EQ.. you embrace the ones you find that actually follow the golden rule, and scowl at the ones that abuse it. <p><IMG SRC="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/llowe/qindyin.jpg" ALT="Qindyin's Signature"><BR>
