And NO, it's not &quot;The victims&quot; fault most of those times. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/uoxoxoxoxox.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oxoxo Xoxox</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalRainbow.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Don'</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/28/02 11:12:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2494.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www2.swmed.edu/libraryis/eq/wizsig4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kitting, and things Druid need to realize...</span><hr size=1> You need to petition and /report.  that is the ONLY way you will get someone that is continuously training you.  a Guide will come down invis and watch it once and the trainer will get a warning.  <p>Baroness <b><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68788'>Oxoxo Xoxox</a></b> Sorcerer<BR><b><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235386'>Yumkin Stumpyshorts</a></b> Cleric<BR>
<A HREF="http://www.mithrilweb.com" target="blank"><img src="http://www.queensidecastle.com/eq/Sorcerersig3.jpg" border="0"></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/udiako.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Diako</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/28/02 11:19:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2494.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kitting, and things Druid need to realize...</span><hr size=1> hehe...  As I tried to defend myself in ooc, being told I shouldn't spam this issue (1 ooc = spamming to that individual).  I didn't get to target the trouble maker.  Didn't ask the other group if they noticed a name, but that was like 15 min later and had my focus back into Exp'ing.  If I had a name, I probably would have cussed him/her out.<br>
<br>
It's mute at this point.  But I can &quot;now&quot; relate to all those that have died to Quadding/kitting.  And I have no respect for the Druids using the &quot;You must have done something&quot; defense.   Cause that is totally not true.  If the druid is out of reach, the Druid made Mistake #1... that mob can agro on anything that it crosses its' path. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/ufoolbok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Foolbok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/28/02 11:54:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2494.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> aye, I am familiar with your woes in EW.  All of Friday night and Saturday morning I set up camp at the tree.  Maybe two hours after I've been there on Friday, Sentry logs on (think that's his name).  He's a ranger that starts to kite to the left of us, we don't go in his area nor does he mess with ours (partner being a 37 sk and I being a 36 shammy).<br>
<br>
[insert Saturday's events here]<br>
<br>
Sunday when I log my friend I start looking for a new spot to level because the Northern shore is being over ran by kiters.  Sentry was back (no disrepect man), some druid that started with a B, and another that started with a Y.  With three kiters right next too each other it'd be suicide to stay there, so we headed to the bridge and checked out the orc camp.  No one was there, not even a soul setting up camp to hunt kod's and snow griffans by the ramp.  The SK pulls the two orcs and of course I root the other ..blah blah aboot other shammy battle stuff involving cancel magic, slow, debuff, buffing, etc...  During this time I see Sentry asking for help in ooc, i ooc back that he shouldn't have kited more then he could handle <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  Sentry ooc'ed back that he was cross trained by another  druid, and that it wasn't his fault.  I replied that I wished him the best of luck and apologized.  My partner and I pulled the other two orcs and mystic, then took a med break.  Both of us were low on health and mana from the previous battle--during the battle there was ooc from a druid who's name starts with a B that was asking for help.  Even while we med'ed up he still persisted on someone helping him--the SK had around 80h and 20m while I had 60 health/mana.  Next thing I know he and some other druid that starts with y has trained two snow dervs and a cougar onto my tank.  Did the cc with root and we finished one cougar and derv, during the first derv my root broke so I turned around to run to get some distance.  When I turned I saw the two people that had trained us go invisi on the slope =/--they're glitter stayed there and did not go up hill like they were zoning.  The last derv broke root and I had aboot 20h left--after two resisted roots and one interrupted one I was dead.<br>
<br>
At this time I was livid--mainly at myself (have a strive to be better thang)  but also at the two that trained us.  When I zoned back into EW I made the ooc comment, &quot;thanks for helping with that train you dumped on my tank's head. /rude&quot;.  Druid B acted all innocent and claimed that he told druid Y to zone, he also stated that it wouldn't have mattered because they were both 00m.  /sigh I said to myself OFWSH, notch some more druids that are incompetent to their class and giving good druids on our server a bad rap.<br>
<br>
